The paper deals with the application of deep learning in remote sensing image analysis, specifically in cloud removal. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the lack of data sets for training neural networks, which is a common issue in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves image processing and analysis, which falls under the graphics (cs.GR) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
